               <bibl>Sijpesteijn PJ, ZPE 106, 218-219, 1995, Pl. VId -- XXII, 15783 -- Line 2: Chairemon can hardly be a ko[mogrammateus Karanidos], as he would then have had to write to the strategos of the Herakleidou meris; he must have been village secretary of a village of the Themistou meris or of the Polemonos meris. (PH).</bibl>
